{"id":"258211326_Caristi's_type_mappings_on_complete_partial_metric_spaces","abstract":"We introduce a new type of Caristi’s mapping on partial metric spaces and show that a partial metric space is complete if and only if every Caristi mapping has a fixed point. From this result we deduce a characterization of bicomplete weightable quasi-metric spaces. Several illustrative examples are given.","authors":["Özlem Acar","Ishak Altun","Salvador Romaguera"],"meta":["January 2013Fixed Point Theory 14(1):3-10"],"references":["261834283_On_Banach_fixed_point_theorems_for_partial_metric_spaces","251515796_Generalized_contractions_on_partial_metric_spaces","251411972_Generalizations_of_Caristi_Kirk's_Theorem_on_Partial_Metric_Spaces","241080625_Completeness_in_quasi-metric_spaces_and_Ekeland_Variational_Principle","238589776_Banach's_Fixed_Point_Theorem_for_Partial_Metric_Spaces","222478359_PCF_extended_with_real_numbers","50282950_Fixed_Point_Theorems_for_Monotone_Mappings_on_Partial_Metric_Spaces","40892135_A_Kirk_Type_Characterization_of_Completeness_for_Partial_Metric_Spaces","268651375_Caristi's_fixed_point_theorem_and_metric_convexity","265463293_Fixed_point_theorems_for_quasi-metric_spaces","243078335_The_Fixed_Point_Theory_for_Mappings_Satisfying_Inwardness_Conditions","231896884_Periodic_and_fixed_point_theorems_in_a_quasi-metric_space","227656324_Partial_Metric_Topology","225396471_Bicompleting_weightable_quasi-metric_spaces_and_partial_metric_spaces","223001960_A_characterization_of_partial_metrizability_Domains_are_quantifiable","220317236_Some_new_extensions_of_Banach's_contraction_principle_to_partial_metric_space","220173501_Partial_metrisability_of_continuous_posets","220173481_A_quantitative_computational_model_for_complete_partial_metric_spaces_via_formal_balls","220173402_The_space_of_formal_balls_and_models_of_quasi-metric_spaces","2513449_Approximation_of_Metric_Spaces_by_Partial_Metric_Spaces"]}